.TH DEJATOP 1 "June 2026" "Version 1.0.0-beta" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dejatop \- Seamless, zero-dependency Desktop Entry Creator for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dejatop
.IR <path/to/executable> " [" \fIoptions\fR ]
.br
.B dejatop
.B --replace-icon
.IR <name> " " <icon_path>
.br
.B dejatop
.B --delete
.IR <name>
.br
.B dejatop
.B --list
.br
.B dejatop
.B --version
.br
.B dejatop
.B --help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B DejaTop
is a fast, zero-dependency CLI utility that automatically generates
.I .desktop
entries for Linux native apps, AppImages, GOG games, and Windows games
run through Wine or Steam Proton (including GE-Proton).
.PP
When passed a path to an executable, DejaTop will automatically detect
the best runner, scan Steam (native and Flatpak), Heroic Games Launcher,
and Lutris for an existing Proton prefix, pick the best available icon
(or extract one dynamically from a .exe if icoutils is installed),
and generate the desktop entry \[em] with zero user interaction needed.
A bash completion script is also provided for seamless tab completion.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-name " \fIname\fR"
Override the auto-detected game name.
.TP
.BR \-\-icon " \fIpath\fR"
Override the auto-detected icon with a specific file path.
.TP
.BR \-\-runner " \fInative|wine|proton\fR"
Override the auto-detected runner.
.TP
.BR \-\-prefix " \fIpath\fR"
Override the Wine/Proton prefix path. Useful when you know the exact
Steam compatdata folder to use.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-\-replace-icon \fIname\fR \fIicon_path\fR
Case-insensitively swaps the icon of an existing DejaTop desktop entry.
If the entry has no Icon= line, one is appended automatically.
.TP
.B \-\-delete \fIname\fR
Case-insensitively deletes a desktop entry and its associated wrapper script.
.TP
.B \-\-list
Lists all desktop entries currently managed by DejaTop.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Displays the current version of DejaTop.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Displays the help message.
.SH PREFIX DISCOVERY
For Windows
.I .exe
files, DejaTop searches for an existing Proton prefix in the following order:
.PP
1. Steam (native): ~/.local/share/Steam/userdata/*/config/shortcuts.vdf
.br
2. Steam (Flatpak): ~/.var/app/com.valvesoftware.Steam/data/Steam/userdata/
.br
3. Heroic Games Launcher: ~/.config/heroic/GamesConfig/*.json
.br
4. Lutris: ~/.config/lutris/games/*.yml
.PP
If no prefix is found, the user is prompted interactively whether to
create a shared DejaTop prefix.
.SH PROTON SELECTION
DejaTop selects Proton in the following priority order:
.PP
1. Latest GE-Proton (e.g., GE-Proton9-27)
.br
2. Latest official Steam Proton (e.g., Proton \- Experimental)
.br
3. If neither is found, DejaTop exits with a clear error message.
.SH NOTES
.PP
Scripts
.RI ( .sh )
and AppImages
.RI ( .AppImage )
are always treated as native executables. Proton/prefix logic is
exclusively triggered for
.I .exe
files.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a desktop entry for a Windows game (auto prefix + Proton):
.B dejatop /mnt/Games/MyGame/game.exe
.TP
Override the name:
.B dejatop /mnt/Games/MyGame/game.exe --name "My Game"
.TP
Create a native entry for an AppImage:
.B dejatop /home/user/apps/app.AppImage --name "My App"
.TP
Force a specific Steam prefix:
.B dejatop /path/to/game.exe --prefix ~/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/compatdata/3848358784
.TP
Fix a wrong icon (case-insensitive):
.B dejatop --replace-icon "assassin" /path/to/icon.png
.TP
Remove an entry:
.B dejatop --delete "portal"
.TP
List all managed entries:
.B dejatop --list
.SH KNOWN ISSUES (BETA)
.TP
\(bu Steam Flatpak GE-Proton: prefix discovery works, but running Proton from outside the Flatpak sandbox requires a flatpak-run wrapper (not yet implemented).
.TP
\(bu GOG Galaxy and standalone Wine prefix discovery are not yet implemented.
